<p style="padding:5px 0;font-family:'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-weight: 400;font-size:16px;line-height:25.6px;margin:0;"><strong>Howdy.<img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/2600.png" alt="☀" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /></strong></p>
<p style="padding:5px 0;font-family:'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-weight: 400;font-size:16px;line-height:25.6px;margin:0;">If you have ever argued yourself in circles about a life decision, a career move, or something deeply unhinged you saw on the timeline, Zikoko&#8217;s new show is a support group for you.&nbsp;</p>
<p style="padding:5px 0;font-family:'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-weight: 400;font-size:16px;line-height:25.6px;margin:0;">In the pilot episode of <em>Overthinkers Anonymous</em>, co-hosts Deji Osikoya and Osato Edokpayi sit down with Seye Bandele, co-founder and chief executive officer of Nigerian HR-tech startup PaidHR, for the kind of conversation that goes everywhere at once.</p>
<p style="padding:5px 0;font-family:'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-weight: 400;font-size:16px;line-height:25.6px;margin:0;">Bandele recalls a moment in 2020 when an HR director looked at what he and his co-founder were building and passed. They kept going anyway, for five more months, until someone paid them ₦4 million ($10,000 at the time) to use the product.&nbsp;</p>
